body: Can you paste the crash report? It can be found in the `Console.app`.
Updating to v0.31.x requires a recompilation of your native modules, can you remove `node_modules` and install it again?

Thank you for responding :smile: .
I removed `node_modules` and `npm install` again, but same probrem occured.
Did you re-run `electron-rebuild` to rebuild native modules after `npm install` ([details](https://github.com/atom/electron/blob/master/docs/tutorial/using-native-node-modules.md))?

You can't use `npm install` directly, you have to follow [Using native Node modules
](http://electron.atom.io/docs/v0.31.0/tutorial/using-native-node-modules/) or use `electron-rebuild` to install mongoose because it includes a native module.
